NOTES
              
conditinal satements:
1.to make the set instructions(bolck of instructions) execute when the given condition  is true
2.used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip bases on the given condition

Codition:an expression that evaluates an result(true or false)
Example:console.log(5>6)
Methods:
If
only one possible condition
If the condition is true it will execute otherwise it skip
Syntax:
If(condition){
//code
}
Example
    let a=4
        let b=5
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hello write","<br>")
        }
        document.write("js")
if condition true it executes both 
if false only out of block is executed
output:
hello write
js
If-else:
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hello write","<br>")
        }else{
        document.write("js","<br>")

        }
        document.write("code")
if condition is false it executes else block and out of block code

Else if
 let age=prompt("Enter your age:")
        let name=prompt("Enter your name:")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name+"you are too young to marry")
        }else if(age>35){
            alert(name+"you are to old to marry")

        }else {
            alert(name+"perfect age  to marry")
        }
        alert("welcome to my world")
       

